{"art": [], "author": [{"email_address": "sowen@statesman.com", "first_name": "Sue", "id": 265, "last_name": "Owen", "name_slug": "sue-owen", "on_staff_page": null, "phone": null, "photo": null, "publication": {"id": 3, "publication_name": "Austin American-Statesman", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/3/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/265/", "title": "PolitiFact Texas staff writer", "twitter": null}], "canonical_url": "/texas/statements/2012/dec/20/larry-kilgore/larry-kilgore-says-texas-economy-about-30-percent-/", "edition": {"adkey": "Editions", "advalue": "Texas", "edition": "Texas", "edition_slug": "texas", "has_afterthefact": false, "id": 2, "index_page": false, "meter_name": "The Texas Truth-O-Meter", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/edition/2/"}, "editor": [{"email_address": "wgstexas@gmail.com", "first_name": "W. Gardner", "id": 122, "last_name": "Selby", "name_slug": "w-gardner-selby", "on_staff_page": 84, "phone": "", "photo": null, "publication": {"id": 3, "publication_name": "Austin American-Statesman", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/3/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/122/", "title": "Former PolitiFact Texas editor", "twitter": ""}], "facebook_headline": null, "id": 7192, "in_future": false, "is_pundit": false, "make_public": true, "preview": true, "researcher": [{"email_address": "sowen@statesman.com", "first_name": "Sue", "id": 265, "last_name": "Owen", "name_slug": "sue-owen", "on_staff_page": null, "phone": null, "photo": null, "publication": {"id": 3, "publication_name": "Austin American-Statesman", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/3/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/265/", "title": "PolitiFact Texas staff writer", "twitter": null}], "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statement/7192/", "ruling": {"adkey": "Truth-O-Meter", "advalue": "False", "id": 5, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statementruling/5/", "ruling": "False", "ruling_graphic": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/rulings/tom-false.png", "ruling_slug": "false"}, "ruling_comments": "<p>\r\n\tAs tens of thousands of signatures piled up on a petition for Texas to withdraw from the United States, Larry Kilgore of Arlington told <em>The New York Times</em> that the state could stand on its own.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\t&quot;Our economy is about 30 percent larger than that of Australia,&quot; Kilgore said in a Nov. 23, 2012, <em>Times </em><a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2012/11/24/us/politics/with-stickers-a-petition-and-even-a-middle-name-secession-fever-hits-texas.html?_r=1&amp;\">news story</a>.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tWe decided to check that claim and one from the <a href=\"https://petitions.whitehouse.gov/petition/peacefully-grant-state-texas-withdraw-united-states-america-and-create-its-own-new-government/BmdWCP8B\">petition</a> itself, which said Texas &quot;is the 15th largest economy in the world.&quot; That&rsquo;s <a href=\"http://www.politifact.com/texas/statements/2012/dec/18/texas-petition/secession-petition-says-texas-has-15th-largest-eco/\">True</a>.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tFirst, we set aside pretty much all considerations of practicality, because secession would upend a number of factors affecting the Texas economy. Besides, as <em>Austin American-Statesman</em> humor writer John Kelso observed in a Dec. 8, 2012, <a href=\"http://www.statesman.com/news/news/local-govt-politics/kelso-if-texas-secedes-somebody-remember-to-bring-/nTQWy/\">column</a>, nearly 25 million Texans hadn&rsquo;t signed it.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tKilgore has run for numerous offices in Texas since 2004 as a pro-secession candidate. His basis for this statement, he told us by phone, was a comparison of nations&rsquo; gross domestic product to that of Texas.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tGDP is the most-used measure of national economic output, <a href=\"http://www.bea.gov/scb/account_articles/national/0398niw/maintext.htm\">defined</a> as the market value of the goods and services produced by labor and property within the country.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tKilgore said he drew his numbers from <a href=\"http://www.nationmaster.com/index.php\">NationMaster</a>, a Sydney, Australia-based website that <a href=\"http://mathforum.org/library/view/69473.html\">compares</a> nations and U.S. states on matters from health and crime to economy, using data from many <a href=\"http://www.nationmaster.com/statistics/sources\">sources</a> to generate lists and graphs.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tNationMaster&rsquo;s <a href=\"http://www.nationmaster.com/country/as-australia/eco-economy\">Australia page</a> gives the country&rsquo;s GDP as $606 billion, citing &quot;Economic Importance, 1998&quot; as its source. The site&rsquo;s Texas page gives the <a href=\"http://www.statemaster.com/state/TX-texas/eco-economy\">gross state product</a> as $881 billion, citing U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics information from March 2006.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tSo although the numbers are both presented as current data on the website, and they show Texas&rsquo; GDP to be 45 percent larger than Australia&rsquo;s, they appear to represent the Texas economy in 2006 and the Australian economy in 1998.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\t&quot;Are you serious? My goodness,&quot; Kilgore said, when we asked if he&rsquo;d known the site was using data that old. &quot;I guess we need some more updated numbers.&quot; He had not looked at the sources, he said, and didn&rsquo;t do further research.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tThe Texas state comptroller&rsquo;s office annually <a href=\"http://www.governor.state.tx.us/files/ecodev/IfTXWereANation.pdf\">calculates</a> where Texas would rank globally if it were a nation. Spokesman RJ DeSilva told us by email that the comptroller uses the GDP calculated for Texas by the federal Bureau of Economic Statistics and sent us the 2011 figure: $1.3 trillion.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tBy phone, bureau spokesman Thomas Dail suggested we compare the Texas figure to national GDP calculated with current prices in U.S. dollars. That would be &quot;conceptually consistent,&quot; he said.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tDail guided us through the steps of generating the <a href=\"http://www.bea.gov/iTable/iTable.cfm?ReqID=70&amp;step=1\">Texas statistics</a> on his agency&rsquo;s website. Separately, we found a <a href=\"http://www.dfat.gov.au/geo/fs/aust.pdf\">fact sheet</a> from the Australian Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade with the country&#39;s annual GDPs using current prices and U.S. dollars.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n\t&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\r\n\t<table style=\"border:none;border-collapse:collapse\">\r\n\t\t<colgroup>\r\n\t\t\t<col width=\"83\" />\r\n\t\t\t<col width=\"95\" />\r\n\t\t\t<col width=\"104\" />\r\n\t\t\t<col width=\"88\" />\r\n\t\t\t<col width=\"97\" />\r\n\t\t\t<col width=\"88\" />\r\n\t\t</colgroup>\r\n\t\t<tbody>\r\n\t\t\t<tr style=\"height:52px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\tGDP in $US billion</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t2007</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t2008</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t2009</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t2010</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t2011</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t\t<tr style=\"height:0px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://www.bea.gov/iTable/iTable.cfm?ReqID=70&amp;step=1\">Texas</a></p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t1,147.404</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t1,209.267</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t1,129.537</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t1,222.904</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t1,308.132</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t\t<tr style=\"height:0px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://www.dfat.gov.au/geo/fs/aust.pdf\">Australia</a></p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t944.8</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t1,033.5</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t976.0</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t1,242.1</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t1,487.4</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t\t<tr style=\"height:0px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\tWho&rsquo;s bigger?</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\tTexas</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t21% bigger</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\tTexas</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t17% bigger</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\tTexas</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t16% bigger</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\tAustralia</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t2% bigger</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t\t<td style=\"border:1px solid #000000;vertical-align:top;padding:7px 7px 7px 7px\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: left; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\tAustralia 12% bigger</p>\r\n\t\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t</tbody>\r\n\t</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n\t<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tThe bureau&rsquo;s data and the Australian government&rsquo;s numbers show that Texas&rsquo; GDP was larger than Australia&rsquo;s in 2007 through 2009, but not in 2010 or 2011. For 2011, Australia&rsquo;s GDP of $1.487 billion was 12 percent larger than Texas&rsquo; $1.308 billion GDP.<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\t<strong>Our ruling</strong><br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tKilgore said Texas&rsquo; economy is 30 percent larger than Australia&rsquo;s, but that was based on mismatched, outdated figures. We rate his statement as False.</p>\r\n", "ruling_comments_date": "2012-12-19T19:26:15.014036", "ruling_date": "2012-12-20T10:00:00", "ruling_headline": "Larry Kilgore says Texas economy is about 30 percent larger than Australia\u2019s", "ruling_headline_slug": "larry-kilgore-says-texas-economy-about-30-percent-", "ruling_link_text": "Kangaroo outweighs armadillo", "ruling_state": null, "source_documents": null, "sources": "<p>\r\n\tThe New York Times news story,<a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2012/11/24/us/politics/with-stickers-a-petition-and-even-a-middle-name-secession-fever-hits-texas.html?_r=0\"> &quot;With Stickers, a Petition and Even a Middle Name, Secession Fever Hits Texas,</a>&quot; Nov. 23, 2012<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tTelephone and email interviews with Larry Kilgore, Dec. 5-18, 2012<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tEmail <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/12tRed_8Otn0Ylxf-F1iWmYH8Pz3Y710vU5uBtF6P0oI/edit\">interviews</a> (excerpted) with Peter Allison, economic consultant to Kilgore campaign, Dec. 17-18, 2012<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tEmail interviews with RJ DeSilva, spokesman for Texas comptroller&rsquo;s office, Dec. 6-14, 2012<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tTelephone and email interviews with Thomas Dail, public affairs specialist at U.S. Bureau of Economic Analysis, Dec. 10-18, 2012<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tEmail interviews with Matthias Rumpf, chief media officer for Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development, Dec. 11-12, 2012<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tEmail interview with Susan Fridy, senior manager for public affairs for Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development, Dec. 14, 2012<br />\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tEmail interviews with Paulina Acuna, communication officer, Office of the Statistician and External Engagement at the Australian Bureau of Statistics, Dec. 16-17, 2012</p>\r\n", "speaker": {"adkey": null, "advalue": null, "barely_true_count": 0, "current_job": "", "false_count": 1, "first_name": "Larry", "half_true_count": 0, "home_state": "", "id": 2125, "last_name": "Kilgore", "mostly_true_count": 0, "name_slug": "larry-kilgore", "pants_count": 0, "party": {"id": 3, "party": "Republican", "party_slug": "republican", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/party/3/"}, "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/mugs/Kilgoremugsquare.jpg", "primary_edition": {"adkey": "Editions", "advalue": "Texas", "edition": "Texas", "edition_slug": "texas", "has_afterthefact": false, "id": 2, "index_page": false, "meter_name": "The Texas Truth-O-Meter", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/edition/2/"}, "promise_meter_cutout": null, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/person/2125/", "total_count": 1, "true_count": 0, "website": "http://secedekilgore.com/"}, "statement": "<p>\r\n\tSays Texas economy is about 30 percent larger than Australia&rsquo;s.</p>\r\n", "statement_context": "a New York Times news story", "statement_date": "2012-11-23", "statement_type": {"id": 2, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statementtype/2/", "statement_type": "Claim", "type_description": "blog post "}, "subject": [{"description": "", "id": 4, "photo": null, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/subject/4/", "subject": "Economy", "subject_slug": "economy", "used_in_edition": []}, {"description": "", "id": 147, "photo": null, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/subject/147/", "subject": "States", "subject_slug": "states", "used_in_edition": []}], "target": [], "twitter_headline": ""}